  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "The docs for the truffle v5 plugin recommend `npm install web3@1.0.0-beta.37` but unless this is done using the `--save-exact` flag subsequent installations of a project (ex: in CI) will install higher versions and trigger:\r\n```\r\nError BDLR802: Plugin @nomiclabs/buidler-truffle5 requires web3 version 1.0.0-beta.37 but got 1.0.0-beta.55.\r\nIf you haven't installed web3 manually, please run: npm install --save-dev web3@1.0.0-beta.37\r\nIf you have installed web3 yourself, please reinstall it with a valid version.\r\n```\r\n(This is a great error! Buidler's error management is excellent.) ",
